data.16: Conditions Other Than Standard Temperature and Pressure
data.24: Air-dried Basis - A condition representative of a partially dried sample
data.25: As-received Basis - A condition representative of a sample as it arrived at a laboratory, before any processing or conditioning
data.26: Dry Basis - A condition representative of no moisture in the sample
data.27: Equilibrium Basis - A condition representative of material in its natural state
data.28: Moisture and Ash-Free Basis - A condition representative of no moisture and no ash in the sample
data.29: Oxidizing Atmosphere - The presence of oxidizing gases during testing
data.30: Reducing Atmosphere - The presence of reducing gases during testing
data.32: Scaled Weight - A weight that is taken from a scale rather than calculated
data.35: Saturated Vapor - Measurement applies to the maximum amount of product material that can be held in vapor form without condensing
data.36: Unconditional - Measurement applies with no further conditions beyond those already specified
data.37: Short-term - Measurement applies only over the short-term specified
data.38: Time-weighted - Measurement signifies that the measurement for each event is weighted by the time duration of that event
data.44: Average - Calculated Value was based on an average parameter or standard
data.45: Per Gallon - Calculated Value was based on per gallon parameter or standard
data.56: Real Estate Owned or Corporate Owned
